<section class="bg-base-200 min-h-screen py-20">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">WHAT IS OSR?</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-base-content/70">
        Discover the Old-School Renaissance
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm mb-8">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title text-2xl">The Basics</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            OSR stands for "Old-School Renaissance" or "Old-School Revival". It
            refers to both a style of play and a movement within tabletop
            roleplaying games that seeks to recapture the spirit of early RPGs
            from the 1970s and 1980s.
          </p>
          <p>
            Rather than focusing on character builds, balanced encounters, and
            predetermined story arcs, OSR games emphasize player skill,
            exploration, emergent storytelling, and the possibility of real
            failure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm mb-8">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title text-2xl">Core Principles</h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-4">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">
                Player Skill Over Character Skill
              </h3>
              <p>
                Success depends on clever thinking and problem-solving, not just
                dice rolls and character stats.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Rulings, Not Rules</h3>
              <p>
                The GM makes quick decisions to keep the game moving rather than
                consulting rulebooks for every situation.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Deadly and Fair</h3>
              <p>
                The world doesn't scale to your level. Danger is real, but
                information is freely given so you can make informed choices.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Exploration and Discovery</h3>
              <p>
                The focus is on exploring dangerous places, finding treasure,
                and uncovering mysteries in a living world.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm mb-8">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title text-2xl">How is it Different?</h2>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
            <table class="table table-zebra">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>OSR Games</th>
                  <th>Modern D&D (5e)</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Characters are fragile, death is common</td>
                  <td>Characters are heroic from level 1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Exploration and problem-solving focus</td>
                  <td>Combat and storytelling focus</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Simple, light rules</td>
                  <td>Detailed mechanics and options</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>GM improvisation and rulings</td>
                  <td>Rules as written (RAW)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Player ingenuity matters most</td>
                  <td>Character abilities matter most</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm mb-8">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title text-2xl">Popular OSR Systems</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            The OSR encompasses many different game systems, including:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong>Old-School Essentials</strong> - A streamlined version of classic
              Basic D&D
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Dungeon Crawl Classics</strong> - High-variance dice and pulp
              fantasy chaos
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Cairn</strong> - Minimalist rules, maximum adventure
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Mothership</strong> - Sci-fi horror in space
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>MÃ¶rk Borg</strong> - Doom metal album meets RPG
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Knave</strong> - Classless, simple, and compatible
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title text-2xl">Ready to Try It?</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            The best way to understand OSR is to experience it! OZ ORC features
            games across the entire OSR spectrum, from classic dungeon crawls to
            weird sci-fi adventures.
          </p>
          <p>
            Whether you're a veteran of old-school gaming or completely new to
            RPGs, our experienced GMs will guide you through unforgettable
            adventures.
          </p>
          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Back to Main Page</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
